definitions.definition: A pipe , tube or canal which carries gas or liquid from one place to another

subdefinitions.definition: An enclosure or channel for electrical cable runs , telephone cables, or other conductors
A vessel for conveying lymph or glandular secretions such as tears or bile
A tube or elongated cavity (such as a xylem vessel ) for conveying water , sap , or air

definitions.definition: A layer (as in the atmosphere or the ocean ) which occurs under usually abnormal conditions and in which radio or sound waves are confined to a restricted path

main_definition: A pipe , tube or canal which carries gas or liquid from one place to another
secondary_definitions: ( physics ) A layer (as in the atmosphere or the ocean ) which occurs under usually abnormal conditions and in which radio or sound waves are confined to a restricted path
